Ford GoBike data analysis¶

by Bertrand B¶

Investigation Overview¶

In my investigation I want to explore this dataset to undersatnd the differents part of It. I will show trends in the dataset, the interesting fact we can get out of It. In this case I want to show the different place someone will got to using the ford GoBike, the duration of his trips and more info about It.

Dataset Overview¶

This dataset is composed of users of GoBike application by ford wich register your trip, the duration of It, the localistion of It (using lat and longitude) and the type of users.

Univariate Visualization¶

The next visualization are univariates one to understand the variables well before computing It with other variables. I will plot the start hour, the end hour (of the trip), the type of user and the duration of the trip.

The majority of users (around 80%) are Subscribers and rest is Customers. The mean duration of a trip is around 1000 sec as the plot show It, but there are some outliers that keep their trips last > 5000 sec (83 hour). Maybe they didn't disconnect from the GoBike appli ?

We can see tends in the starting hour and in the end hour. At 7 and 8 am there is a peak, maybe people go to work or start their day. And we see an other big peak at 4 pm.

Positions of the trips¶

With the longitude and the latitude we can plot the position on a 2D graph or even more with a web tool like kepler.

Distance of the trips by user types¶

We can plot the distance that I computed by the different users and by categories of positions. Now wa have the three positions that I assigned 'San Fransisco', 'Oakland' and 'San José'.

In [17]:
plt.figure(figsize=[16,5])
plt.subplot(1,3,1)
sb.barplot(data=df,x='user_type',y='distance_m',hue='label_name');
plt.title('Distance between user types')
plt.subplot(1,3,2)
sb.violinplot(data=df,x='user_type',y='distance_m',hue='label_name');
plt.ylabel('')
plt.ylim([-8000,30000])
plt.title('Distance between user types');
The trip distance is the same for subscribers and Customers but the trips that start from San Fransisco and San José tend to last much longer than the trips from Oakland.
